[1]
Date: 7 Nov 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: India Express, 30 Oct 2004 [accessed 7 Nov 2004, edited]
<http://www.indiaexpress.com/news/regional/uttar_pradesh/20041030-0.html>

Mystery disease toll in Uttar Pradesh rises to 98
-----------------------------------------------
6 more lives were claimed by the mystery disease stalking western Uttar
Pradesh, taking the death toll to 98 today [30 Oct 2004]. The
worst-affected district of Sahranpur, where the disease is afflicting
children, had 50 deaths, including 6 since last evening [29 Oct 2004]. All
of the 6 deaths took place in Nangal town of the Sahranpur district. 2 of
them died in the hospital, official sources said in Ghaziabad.
District Magistrate Bhagpat Kamini Ratan Chauhan said that the number of
ailing children was on the rise, even though there were no new deaths. The
disease has so far claimed 14 lives in Bhagpat.
According to doctors, all cases appeared to be of viral encephalitis, as
the brains of the children had been affected.
--
